{
  "name": "Eye Bleed",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/blood.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When using the Bleed ability, you may increase the target&#8217;s blood pressure, rupturing vessels in the affected creature&#8217;s eyes for the duration of the bleed damage. The creature suffers a 20% miss chance from concealment against all creatures for the duration of the bleed damage. If you spend an additional spell point, the creature is instead blinded for the duration of the bleed damage as blood streams from around its eyes. Creature&#8217;s without eyes or equivalent sensory organs are immune to this effect.</p>\n",
